<p>A good rule is that 1 minute of vigorous activity provides the same health benefits as 2 minutes of moderate activity.</p>

<p>One way to do your recommended 150 minutes of weekly physical activity is to do 30 minutes on 5 days every week.</p>

<p>All adults should also break up long periods of sitting with light activity.</p>

<p>Source: NHS </p>
